 hVdrsp pf-3715_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Every year, the UK marks a week-long celebration of one of its most iconic culinary treasures: the pie. National Pie Week, observed in the first full week of March, is a testament to the nation's enduring love for pies and a vibrant reminder of Britain's rich culinary heritage. Originating from the initiative of Jus-Rol in 2007, this delicious week serves both as a homage to the pie's storied past in British cuisine, dating back to the 12th century, and as a beacon for culinary innovation.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-3717_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-3718_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-3719_">A pie for every palate - Understanding the celebration</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-3721_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">At its core, National Pie Week is an invitation to explore the diverse world of pies, from savoury classics filled with steak and kidney to sweet creations brimming with apples and blackberries. It's a time when local bakeries, pubs, and restaurants across the UK showcase their culinary prowess through special menus and pie-themed promotions, drawing in pie aficionados and curious foodies alike.</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-3723_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/rustic-open-pies-with-apricots-and-raspberry-fren-2023-11-27-05-36-03-utc.jpg?v=1709892004" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/rustic-open-pies-with-apricots-and-raspberry-fren-2023-11-27-05-36-03-utc.jpg?v=1709892004 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/rustic-open-pies-with-apricots-and-raspbe